===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|oter|lang=ang}}. Cognate with Old High German {{term|ottar}}, Old Slavic {{Glag|ⰲⱏⰺⰴⱃⰰ}}, and Ancient Greek {{term|ὕδρα}} (“Hydra”, “water snake”). More etymology under English [[water]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈɒt.ə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑː.tɚ/}}
* {{rhymes|ɒtə(r)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any [[aquatic]] or [[marine]] [[carnivorous]] [[mammal]], member of the family ''[[Mustelidae]]'', which also includes [[weasel]]s, [[polecat]]s, [[badger]]s, and others.
# a hairy man, thin, not heavyset, especially one who is gay (c.f. [[bear]])

